# How ANOVA Partitions Variation

ANOVA gets to the global question by partitioning the total variation in the response into two components:

- variation among the group means;
- variation within the groups.

If the group means differ more than we would expect from within-group variation alone, the ANOVA result becomes large enough to reject $H_0$. This partition is illustrated in @fig-anova-decomposition. This partition is illustrated in @fig-anova-decomposition.


